Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat: user-employee integrity, supplier UI removal, shift
 cash flow integration

SINGLE-BRANCH ARCHITECTURE ENHANCEMENTS:

Phase 1 - Suppliers UI Removal:
- Removed Suppliers navigation item from main_shell.dart
- Commented out /suppliers route from app_router.dart
- Retained suppliers table and data layer for FK safety
- Supplier transactions still tracked for shift cash flow

Phase 2 - User-Employee Integrity:
- Created EmployeeResolverService to guarantee employee context
- Service provides getEmployeeForUser() that returns existing or creates new
- Auto-provisions employees on user registration via AuthService
- Resolves employee on login if user has no employee link
- Added migration to ensure employees.branch_id NOT NULL DEFAULT '1'
- Added index idx_users_employee_id for faster lookups

Logging Tags:
- [EMPLOYEE_PROVISIONED] - New employee created for user
- [EMPLOYEE_RESOLVED] - Found existing employee for user
- [EMPLOYEE_ALREADY_EXISTS] - Employee already linked to user
- [EMPLOYEE_AUTO_PROVISIONED] - Employee created during registration

Phase 3 - Shift Cash Flow Integration:
- Added getShiftSalesCash() for cash-in from sales
- Added getShiftExpenses() for cash-out expenses
- Added getShiftPurchasePayments() for supplier payments during shift
- Added getShiftDebtPaymentsReceived() placeholder for future credit collection
- Added getShiftCashFlowSummary() for comprehensive cash breakdown
- Added ShiftCashFlowSummary class with cash-in/cash-out components

Phase 4 - Purchase Payment Entry:
- Created PurchasePaymentEntryDialog for lightweight payment recording
- Dialog allows amount, optional invoice number, and notes
- Integrated into FinancialShiftScreen expenses tab
- Purchase payments recorded as 'supplies' category expenses
- Added recordQuickPayment() to SupplierService

